{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Bug}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/GO|species=Cascoon}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Bug|prevnum=267|prev=Beautifly|nextnum=269|next=Dustox|round=none}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Disambig|species=Cascoon}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Cascoon\n|jname=マユルド\n|jtranslit=Mayurudo\n|tmname=Mayuld\n|ndex=268\n|hdex=017\n|sdex=051\n|type1=Bug\n|category=Cocoon\n|height-ftin=2\'04"\n|height-m=0.7\n|weight-lbs=25.4\n|weight-kg=11.5\n|abilitylayout=1\n|ability1=Shed Skin\n|egggroupn=1\n|egggroup1=Bug\n|eggcycles=15\n|evtotal=2\n|evde=2\n|expyield=72<!--41 in Gen V-VI-->\n|oldexp=72\n|lv100exp=1,000,000\n|gendercode=127\n|color=Purple\n|catchrate=120\n|body=01\n|pokefordex=cascoon\n|generation=3\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Cascoon\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'マユルド\'\'\' \'\'Mayuld\'\') is a {{type|Bug}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation III]].\n\nIt [[evolution|evolves]] from {{p|Wurmple}} depending on its [[personality value]], starting at [[level]] 7, and it evolves into {{p|Dustox}} starting at level 10.\n\n==Biology==\nCascoon is a round, cocoon-like Pokémon. It is covered in purple silk, except for two holes where its red eyes are visible. The soft silk hardens into a tough cocoon that is able to endure attacks, and this Pokémon will not move even when it is attacked. However, it never forgets the pain it endures and seeks revenge upon evolution. It lives in {{DL|List of Pokémon by habitat|Forest Pokémon|forests}}, where it hides underneath large leaves and inside the gaps of tree branches. Additionally, it camouflages itself by attaching dead leaves to its body. As its cells create energy for evolution, the inside of the cocoon becomes hot. Cracks start to form in its casing when evolution is near.\n\n==In the anime==\n===In the main series===\n[[File:Jessie Cascoon.png|thumb|left|220px|Cascoon in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n====Major appearances====\n=====[[Jessie\'s Cascoon]]=====\n[[Jessie]]\'s Wurmple evolved into Cascoon in \'\'[[AG024|A Corphish out of Water]]\'\', which also marked the species\' debut. However, Jessie thought that she was a Silcoon. As a result, [[James]] and {{MTR}} were left worried about Jessie\'s rage when Cascoon evolved into Dustox. Fortunately, Jessie was ultimately not disappointed when Cascoon did indeed evolve.\n\n====Minor appearances====\nA {{pkmn|Coordinator}}\'s Cascoon appeared in \'\'[[AG121|Hi Ho Silver Wind!]]\'\'.\n\n===In the Pokémon Omega Ruby and Alpha Sapphire Animated Trailer===\nA Cascoon appeared in the [[Pokémon Omega Ruby and Pokémon Alpha Sapphire Animated Trailer]], where it surrounded {{ga|May}} and her {{p|Torchic}}, only for Torchic to scare it away with a {{type|Fire}} attack.\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:Silcoon Cascoon Adventures.png|thumb|left|200px|Cascoon in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n===In the Pokémon Adventures manga===\nA Cascoon appeared in \'\'[[PS182|Making Mirth with Mightyena]]\'\'.\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Cascoon (TCG)}}\n{{-}}\n==Game data==\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Dex/Header|type=Bug}}\n{{Dex/NA|gen=III}}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=III|reg1=Hoenn|num1=017|reg2=Kanto}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Ruby|t=FFF|entry=Cascoon makes its protective cocoon by wrapping its body entirely with a fine silk from its mouth. Once the silk goes around its body, it hardens. This Pokémon prepares for its [[evolution]] inside the cocoon.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Sapphire|t=FFF|entry=If it is attacked, Cascoon remains motionless however badly it may be hurt. It does so because if it were to move, its body would be weak upon evolution. This Pokémon will also not forget the pain it endured.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Emerald|t=FFF|entry=To avoid detection by its enemies, it hides motionlessly beneath large leaves and in the gaps of branches. It also attaches dead leaves to its body for camouflage.}}\n{{Dex/Entry2|v=FireRed|v2=LeafGreen|entry=Its body, which is made of soft silk, hardens over time. 