on, along with Silcoon, can be seen without the limb protrusions on its body in the anime, all main series games from X and Y onward, and occasionally in {{2v2|HeartGold|SoulSilver}}.\n** However, [[James]]\'s Pokémon trivia cards showed that Silcoon and Cascoon indeed have those limbs.\n* Cascoon is the only {{type|Bug}} cocoon-based Pokémon whose Defense stat does not decrease upon evolution.\n* Cascoon is the only Pokémon found in a [[Friend Safari]] that is not its own type; it is found in the {{type|Poison}} Friend Safari even though Cascoon is pure Bug. However, it evolves into the Poison-type {{p|Dustox}}.\n\n===Origin===\nCascoon is based on the {{wp|Pupa|chrysalis}} or cocoon stage of a {{wp|butterfly}} or {{wp|moth}}.\n\n====Name origin====\nCascoon may be a combination of \'\'cask\'\' (a container, often cylindrical) or \'\'casca\'\' (Portuguese for shell), and \'\'{{wp|Pupa|cocoon}}\'\'. It could also derive from \'\'cast\'\', a shell meant for immobilizing part of the body or the method of creating said shell.\n\nMayuld is a combination of 繭 \'\'mayu\'\' (cocoon) and \'\'shield\'\'.\n\n==In other languages==\n{{Other languages|type=Bug|type2=Bug\n|ja= マユルド \'\'Mayuld\'\'|jameaning=From {{tt|繭 \'\'mayu\'\'|cocoon}} and \'\'shield\'\'\n|fr=Blindalys |frmeaning=From \'\'{{tt|blindage|armoring}}\'\' and \'\'chrysalis\'\'\n|es=Cascoon|esmeaning=Same as English name\n|de=Panekon|demeaning=From {{tt|\'\'Panzer\'\'|armor}} and {{tt|\'\'Kokon\'\'|cocoon}}\n|it=Cascoon|itmeaning=Same as English name\n|ko=카스쿤 \'\'Cascoon\'\'|komeaning=Transliteration of English name\n|zh_cmn=盾甲繭 / 盾甲茧 \'\'Dùnjiǎjiǎn\'\'|zh_cmnmeaning=Literally "Shielded cocoon"\n|hi=कास्कून \'\'Cascoon\'\'|himeaning=Transcription of English name\n|ru=Каскун \'\'Kaskun\'\'|rumeaning=Transcription of English name\n}}\n<br clear="left">\n\n==Related articles==\n* [[Jessie\'s Cascoon]]\n\n==External links==\n\n{{-}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Bug}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Bug|prevnum=267|pre